   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Purpose     : Root Blazor router component for AbsenceApp V2.
                 Matches the current URL to a @page-decorated component and
                 renders it using the V2 BaseLayout shell.
                 Also acts as a lightweight auth guard: subscribes to
                 LocationChanged and redirects unauthenticated users to /login
                 whenever they navigate to any route other than /login.
   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Changes     :
     - 1.0.0  2026-03-13  Initial implementation.
     - 2.0.0  2026-03-23  Switched DefaultLayout to MainLayout for V2 shell.
     - 2.1.0  2026-03-24  Verified for AbsenceAppV2; no functional changes.
     - 2.2.0  2026-03-25  Confirmed as V2 router after V1/V2 project split.
     - 2.3.0  2026-03-25  Fixed DefaultLayout namespace.
     - 2.4.0  2026-03-26  Corrected DefaultLayout to typeof(MainLayoutV2).
     - 2.5.0  2026-03-26  Updated to typeof(BaseLayoutV2).
     - 2.6.0  2026-03-26  Added auth guard + LocationChanged.
     - 2.7.0  2026-03-29  DefaultLayout changed to MainLayoutV2.
     - 2.8.0  2026-04-06  Diagnostic logging added.
     - 2.9.0  2026-04-07  Crash log path unified + caller-origin tag.
     - 2.10.0 2026-04-07  MAUI Hybrid fix: ignore stale WebView navigation
                          events to authenticated routes when not authenticated.
     - 2.11.0 2026-04-07  Added forced redirect to /login after ignoring stale
                          MAUI navigation so the UI renders the correct page.
     - 2.12.0 2026-04-07  Debug instrumentation: added Dispose log.
   ===========================================================================
